129
00:08:19,522 --> 00:08:25,046
It has given me insight to varying labor laws and ways to work within their parameters, policies, and procedures.

130
00:08:25,807 --> 00:08:38,698
I've experienced many different cultures and ways of thinking from city to city, giving me coping mechanisms to maximize the best results working with individuals as well as varying groups in individual cities or towns.

131
00:08:39,773 --> 00:08:45,978
I've learned over the years the art of collaboration and how it can foster true creativity and excellent outcomes.

132
00:08:46,498 --> 00:08:48,920
And above all else, I've been true to who I am.

133
00:08:49,641 --> 00:08:53,003
Those who know me best will tell you I'm a man of my word.

134
00:08:53,904 --> 00:08:58,427
I'm a man that will stick to a code of ethics even though it may not benefit me in getting ahead.

135
00:08:58,988 --> 00:09:05,773
And I'm a firm believer that we are all on the same playing field of life and that no one deserves to be treated any less than anyone else.

136
00:09:06,855 --> 00:09:18,963
In over 30 years of running businesses up and down the East Coast, most notably my own last 15 years of owning a business, I accumulated a parallel amount of knowledge that works well with running a municipality.

137
00:09:20,825 --> 00:09:30,011
Managing and creating budgets for many years, ranging from $1 million to $100 million, I can set up and break down a budget to see where the opportunities lie.

138
00:09:31,354 --> 00:09:46,660
Being my own budget director for my business, I've created and implemented countless budgets, as well as cash flow plans and P&Ls, allowing me to understand the terminology of a budget and where to look for unbalanced monies or inaccurate spending.

139
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:55,643
As a negotiator for many vendors and insurance contracts, I have a keen insight to current issues on negotiating labor contracts.

140
00:09:56,602 --> 00:10:06,031
My commitment is I will never walk away from a negotiation if it makes more sense on both sides to find common ground financially and collaboratively.

141
00:10:07,672 --> 00:10:21,945
I have a long history of taking on and completing large business projects that involved major expansion and business startups, which in turn has given me a unique set of skills needed to complete any project, large or small, for example, the master plan.

142
00:10:23,312 --> 00:10:31,781
This takes good communication, collaboration, planning, timing, and sometimes, and not often addressed, follow-up.

143
00:10:32,863 --> 00:10:38,125
hiring, training, and developing over 5,000 employees in my 30 plus years of running businesses.

144
00:10:39,446 --> 00:10:46,409
I developed a follow-up tools to ensure the success of individuals, for example, performance evaluation and action plans.

145
00:10:47,130 --> 00:10:50,991
This is crucial to the overall morale of any work environment.

146
00:10:51,652 --> 00:10:57,214
People can respect better where they stand once they have had these conversations.

147
00:10:58,195 --> 00:11:02,537
And they have been given achievable goals to be successful at their jobs.

148
00:11:03,794 --> 00:11:11,659
I have created training and development programs for better customer service skills that the employees can use as tools to mold their individual successes.

149
00:11:12,260 --> 00:11:15,582
Let's face it, municipality is the ultimate customer service job.

150
00:11:16,883 --> 00:11:22,507
I take pride in putting the people first when performing a successful task, giving them the well-deserved credit.

151
00:11:23,848 --> 00:11:30,112
I'm not afraid to put myself out in front when we fail and take the responsibility when necessary for the people that work with me.

152
00:11:31,598 --> 00:11:37,672
I have accomplished much in my life and I'm excited for the opportunity to share what I've learned in my own community.

153
00:11:38,843 --> 00:11:42,385
I've been recognized and awarded many times over my business achievements.

154
00:11:42,825 --> 00:11:47,367
I was nominated businessman of the year in my community that I own my business in right now.

155
00:11:48,247 --> 00:11:51,489
I have been vice president and president of the Chamber of Commerce in Salem.

156
00:11:52,069 --> 00:12:01,353
I have worked with a company called Nelson Nygaard, which happens to be the exact same company that worked with Medford in 2005 to create their parking program.

157
00:12:02,113 --> 00:12:07,536
I worked with them for two and a half years to create the parking program in Salem that currently exists today.

158
00:12:08,716 --> 00:12:14,799
I have worked closely with many community groups and have been part of many initiatives to move a city forward and get business going.

159
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:25,605
I've worked closely with several community support groups, like Lifebridge, NAGLI, HAWK, and YMCA, just to speak of a few groups important to me.

160
00:12:26,925 --> 00:12:39,496
Having been taught time and time again in every situation that communication can solve mostly every problem, but you need to know when to listen and to learn and when to act on a situation.

161
00:12:41,517 --> 00:12:46,342
I take great pride in the fact that I'm approachable and my door is open to everyone.

162
00:12:47,483 --> 00:12:52,447
I have always said I cannot fix a problem that I do not know about, so let's talk.

163
00:12:54,262 --> 00:13:02,666
These are the most important issues frustrating citizens that I have met over the past few months, actually several months now, with a lot of walking and two pairs of shoes so far.

164
00:13:03,866 --> 00:13:04,326
Parking.

165
00:13:05,667 --> 00:13:07,127
Let's hold Republic to the fire.

166
00:13:07,688 --> 00:13:10,789
This is the third party company that takes care of our parking program.

167
00:13:11,409 --> 00:13:22,754
And let's eliminate these kiosks once and for all on the streets or discuss a way to eliminate the current contract and create our own in-house program putting Medford citizens to work.

168
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:31,350
Look at a better way to create access to the local businesses that thrive on the in and out business by changing times and signs.

169
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:34,673
Give them the opportunity to take advantage of their type of business.

170
00:13:35,835 --> 00:13:39,959
Infrastructure issues like tree stumps, sidewalks, streets, and of course crosswalks.

171
00:13:40,619 --> 00:13:41,960
Complete streets is not enough.

172
00:13:42,161 --> 00:13:44,023
People say they're not afraid to pay taxes.

173
00:13:44,423 --> 00:13:46,024
They just want results.

174
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:49,881
In this area, I feel the administration is not doing well.

175
00:13:50,701 --> 00:13:57,983
We need to take a portion of the general fund money that is not part of the Complete Streets Project and get certain emergency situations done.

176
00:13:59,303 --> 00:14:05,325
Then we need to set aside annual funds to stay ahead by adding to the Complete Streets Project.

177
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:12,647
To pay for this, we need to create a preventative maintenance line item in the budget and expand on our DPW workforce.

178
00:14:13,670 --> 00:14:21,534
This only makes common sense because you cannot expand a city while shrinking the very department responsible for the work that needs to be done.

179
00:14:24,696 --> 00:14:29,618
If we do not take these steps, then we just end up with an incomplete streets program.

180
00:14:30,279 --> 00:14:32,320
It's time to have a clean and inviting city.

181
00:14:33,457 --> 00:14:35,999
the police, fire station, and safety.

182
00:14:36,019 --> 00:14:40,904
The current mayor committed two years ago to getting the process going in a new facility.

183
00:14:41,404 --> 00:14:52,535
Instead, the mayor put her efforts in a new library that will cost a total of close to $34 million, with $22 million of it going right to the bottom line for the citizens of Medford.

184
00:14:54,765 --> 00:15:07,660
I will have the necessary personnel involved in any conversation regarding the building of a fire and police station to discuss how and where we can count on receiving the money necessary to build the much needed facility before we start the planning.

185
00:15:08,521 --> 00:15:12,125
Hire the grant writer needed for the city so we can start planning on this project.

186
00:15:12,975 --> 00:15:25,468
I will also create a line item for hiring much needed staff that conforms to the projected growth of the city and the amount of fire and police needed to ensure the correct safety for both the citizens and our first responders.

187
00:15:26,388 --> 00:15:32,615
I would also like to revisit another promise not yet completed by the current administration.

188
00:15:33,075 --> 00:15:35,636
Mayor Burke talked about two years ago was foot patrols.

189
00:15:35,977 --> 00:15:43,501
I think that's a great idea, and I think it's time we take a look at that, especially with the issues that we have, including the opioid situation.

190
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:45,702
We need to have foot patrols in our neighborhoods.

191
00:15:46,913 --> 00:15:52,996
And we can pay for this by increasing our increasing tax base by our new construction, so this can happen.

192
00:15:53,997 --> 00:15:58,460
Communication, the lack of good communication between the administration and the city council.

193
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:09,226
The mayor has stated in her most recent article that she created a council liaison for them to go to if they were having issues with the department head, but it was never their role to go to the city council meetings.

194
00:16:09,826 --> 00:16:16,050
Even though Mayor Burke did commit to being at or represented at the city council meetings, neither has happened.

195
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:20,453
I will be at the city council meetings once a month or as requested.

196
00:16:21,334 --> 00:16:42,553
I have the rapport with the city councilors and will continue to foster a better working relationship as well as create workshops with the city councilors, department heads and the administration as well as citizens of Medford in a casual environment to allow for frank, open and creative discussion on ways to move this city forward.

197
00:16:44,082 --> 00:16:54,385
I promise to make sure that I treat the city council as one body for the good of the city, and I vow to eliminate the day-to-day issues that they're faced with, which are not even their responsibility.

198
00:16:54,685 --> 00:16:58,026
For example, hours of conversation about potholes and sidewalks.

199
00:16:58,646 --> 00:17:04,888
We need to move the city forward, and these are not the conversations that the people who are supposed to move the city forward should be having.

200
00:17:05,973 --> 00:17:08,175
That is the DPW's responsibility.

201
00:17:08,575 --> 00:17:14,280
This will allow the council to put forth resolutions that will indeed move the city into the future.

202
00:17:16,082 --> 00:17:16,942
The downtowns.

203
00:17:18,203 --> 00:17:20,625
This is the one that's near and dear to my heart as a business owner.

204
00:17:21,526 --> 00:17:27,912
Although the master plan is and has been a good start for many, many, many years, it is still not enough.

205
00:17:28,112 --> 00:17:30,514
We need to address the Office of Community Development.

206
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:38,449
and overall infrastructure of the administration to better prepare for anticipated growth spurt, this city will incur.

207
00:17:39,851 --> 00:17:44,778
We need to seek out new and inventive small businesses to create excitement in our downtown.

208
00:17:45,599 --> 00:17:49,264
For example, a dessert bar, a rooftop restaurant,

209
00:17:50,368 --> 00:18:01,520
an imported cheese shop, a local artist shop where you can actually take a class and display and or sell your art in that very shop, and many other varying shops that represent different cultures.

210
00:18:02,421 --> 00:18:08,588
This takes an outreach program that may span the globe using today's technology to travel through different shops.

