00:56:30,923 --> 00:56:41,051
Efforts to integrate both schools need to continue with academic opportunities for the students of the voc tech expanding and career and technical opportunities for high school students being cultivated.

624
00:56:42,132 --> 00:56:46,435
New shops as well as renovations and acquiring up-to-date equipment should be a top priority.

625
00:56:47,476 --> 00:56:51,459
I truly believe career and technical education needs to be prioritized.

626
00:56:52,139 --> 00:56:55,742
Not every student will take an academic path toward a four-year college.

627
00:56:56,907 --> 00:57:02,651
We need to make sure the education we provide them ensures they will be well prepared and successful in the careers they chose.

628
00:57:03,592 --> 00:57:08,196
Bolstering our community education offerings could provide revenue to see this progress continue.

629
00:57:09,577 --> 00:57:15,341
My oldest children were among the first class of students to attend the new elementary schools from kindergarten through fifth grade.

630
00:57:16,582 --> 00:57:23,127
Throughout the years, these schools have not been funded for proper maintenance, forcing reactive repairs versus proactive routine yearly maintenance.

631
00:57:23,890 --> 00:57:31,792
In order for these buildings to properly serve Medford students for the long term, it is essential that a proper maintenance schedule be funded and implemented.

632
00:57:33,132 --> 00:57:35,632
My family is fortunate enough to be able to walk to the Roberts.

633
00:57:36,153 --> 00:57:41,394
With that being said, I am acutely aware of the safety challenges students face while traveling to and from school.

634
00:57:42,334 --> 00:57:47,215
Issues with bus safety, overcrowding, and scheduling are recurring each year and should be addressed.

635
00:57:47,735 --> 00:57:52,496
Walkers face their own challenges with dangerous areas for crosswalks or no crosswalks at all.

636
00:57:53,165 --> 00:57:56,607
poor signage for school zones, and accessibility issues.

637
00:57:57,167 --> 00:57:59,789
All children deserve a safe route to and from school.

638
00:58:00,990 --> 00:58:03,951
Choosing to run for school committee was not a decision I made lightly.

639
00:58:04,752 --> 00:58:08,314
The issues listed previously were just part of the catalyst for my decision.

640
00:58:09,054 --> 00:58:12,056
If elected, I would work to be the voice of the parents and the students.

641
00:58:13,057 --> 00:58:16,899
Our schools do not operate solely on paper or within City Hall.

642
00:58:17,759 --> 00:58:22,382
I am determined to take the politics out of the committee and make decisions regarding our schools

643
00:58:23,023 --> 00:58:28,805
a collaboration of all committee members, parents, and administrators, students, and community input.

644
00:58:30,045 --> 00:58:32,566
I respectfully ask for one of your votes on November 7th.

645
00:58:32,826 --> 00:58:33,206
Thank you.

646
00:58:34,386 --> 00:58:35,287
Thank you, Angela.

647
00:58:47,070 --> 00:58:51,292
Friends and neighbors, my name is Michael Leggero, and I'm running for school committee.

648
00:58:51,592 --> 00:58:52,292
Let me tell you why.

649
00:58:53,297 --> 00:58:54,938
Somewhere in Medford, a baby was born.

650
00:58:55,679 --> 00:58:59,901
Lovely, curious, and if anything like my pumpkins, a bit of a troublemaker.

651
00:59:00,702 --> 00:59:04,704
Soon this beautiful child will be entering kindergarten with my son, Kason.

652
00:59:05,665 --> 00:59:11,148
Until I had a child, I could only see the rough outline of responsibility drawn by fatherhood.

653
00:59:12,109 --> 00:59:16,051
Yet being a parent has opened my eyes beyond the circle of my own family.

654
00:59:16,631 --> 00:59:22,655
As a math teacher with over seven years experience, I know education is destiny.

655
00:59:23,743 --> 00:59:28,907
Every kindergartner's future is shaped by the parents and administrators and teachers standing in front of them.

656
00:59:29,847 --> 00:59:31,608
It is an awesome responsibility.

657
00:59:32,029 --> 00:59:34,330
The parents of Medford invest in our school system.

658
00:59:34,891 --> 00:59:39,354
It is your responsibility to elect the most capable candidates onto our school committee.

659
00:59:39,914 --> 00:59:43,637
Thank you for your time and considering my unique set of experiences.

660
00:59:44,574 --> 00:59:47,895
But before I jabber on about myself, let's talk about our schools.

661
00:59:48,535 --> 00:59:56,598
The Mustangs make our city proud, but is it too outrageous to imagine our schools as the best in Massachusetts?

662
00:59:57,558 --> 01:00:02,620
In the 80s, Medford was placed at the top of almost every school ranking in Massachusetts.

663
01:00:03,220 --> 01:00:06,561
People traveled the world to visit our schools, believe it or not.

664
01:00:07,821 --> 01:00:10,502
Now, well, we've fallen into the middle of the pack.

665
01:00:11,235 --> 01:00:11,455
U.S.

666
01:00:11,495 --> 01:00:19,981
News and World Report ranks Arlington 12th, Somerville 69th, Everett 89th in Massachusetts.

667
01:00:20,862 --> 01:00:23,263
Medford, we didn't even crack into the top 100.

668
01:00:24,724 --> 01:00:29,167
Great Schools, it's an online website, ranks our district 5 out of 10.

669
01:00:31,429 --> 01:00:34,371
Boston Magazine recently ranked Medford 89 out of 125 Boston-area schools.

670
01:00:37,885 --> 01:00:43,889
Our four-year graduation rate has fallen from 87% a few years ago to 80% now.

671
01:00:45,090 --> 01:00:46,751
These rankings are a wake-up call.

672
01:00:47,492 --> 01:00:49,934
All students should aim as high as possible.

673
01:00:50,174 --> 01:00:51,695
Let's not settle for okay.

674
01:00:52,616 --> 01:00:55,578
Let's make our schools the best in Massachusetts.

675
01:00:56,538 --> 01:00:57,119
No, strike that.

676
01:00:57,719 --> 01:01:00,942
Let's play as hard as our musk gangs fight.

677
01:01:01,562 --> 01:01:04,104
Let's be the best school in America.

678
01:01:05,229 --> 01:01:09,133
My teaching career has stretched from Philadelphia to Shanghai.

679
01:01:09,914 --> 01:01:15,599
I have experience teaching mathematics at both elite universities and highly ranked public schools.

680
01:01:16,440 --> 01:01:22,405
I helped build a successful math team in Houston, and I hope you give me the opportunity to fortify the schools here in Medford.

681
01:01:23,313 --> 01:01:26,595
Currently, I run an organic blueberry farm in Massachusetts.

682
01:01:27,176 --> 01:01:29,618
As a small business owner, I know how to stretch a buck.

683
01:01:30,238 --> 01:01:34,121
I know that throwing money at a problem will not solve poor planning.

684
01:01:34,741 --> 01:01:36,803
Customers demand responsive business.

685
01:01:37,283 --> 01:01:40,165
I hope to add this type of responsiveness to our schools.

686
01:01:41,246 --> 01:01:43,207
Here's some plans to help us move forward.

687
01:01:43,908 --> 01:01:46,349
Because Henry won't give me 10 minutes, I only have time for four.

688
01:01:46,970 --> 01:01:49,912
First, we need to make our school committee more accessible.

689
01:01:50,637 --> 01:01:58,121
As a parent of two little boys, I can tell you from personal experience that 6.30 on a weekday is a tough time to make it.

690
01:01:59,021 --> 01:02:08,385
What I suggest is that we rotate our school committee meetings into the weekends, at least once a month, and provide parents with some entertainment for their kids.

691
01:02:08,886 --> 01:02:14,508
This way, excited kids and tired parents will have an opportunity to speak about what's going on with our schools.

692
01:02:16,300 --> 01:02:18,802
Let's extend relationships with the local universities.

693
01:02:19,302 --> 01:02:21,403
Right now we have a really great relationship with Tufts.

694
01:02:22,084 --> 01:02:27,567
Let's look to schools like MIT and Harvard and open internship and lecture opportunities.

695
01:02:28,347 --> 01:02:32,750
Third, we need to reduce the disparities between the schools here in Medford.

696
01:02:33,851 --> 01:02:41,315
The Andrews and the McGlynn, for example, it is unacceptable that poverty rates at one school is half the poverty rate at the other school.

697
01:02:41,756 --> 01:02:43,637
We need to make sure that parity is achieved.

698
01:02:45,235 --> 01:02:49,398
Fourth, let's improve relationships with parents of special needs children.

699
01:02:50,099 --> 01:02:57,464
By far the biggest complaint that I hear as I've been knocking on doors among parents is the resistance to individual education plans.

700
01:02:58,285 --> 01:03:02,408
As a teacher, I acted as a liaison between parents and administrators.

701
01:03:02,968 --> 01:03:05,630
I will continue this work on our school committee.

702
01:03:06,731 --> 01:03:12,335
My campaign is about creating the most successful and transparent school district in Massachusetts.

703
01:03:12,967 --> 01:03:17,750
If you have some time, check out my website, takegovernment.com, or call me directly.

704
01:03:17,970 --> 01:03:21,632
My home number is 781-866-2191.

705
01:03:21,832 --> 01:03:25,394
I'm always happy to talk, hopefully after my boys are in bed.

706
01:03:26,475 --> 01:03:28,316
The children of Medford deserve the best.

707
01:03:28,856 --> 01:03:32,158
Join me, and let's take our schools from good to great.

708
01:03:49,846 --> 01:03:54,568
Hello, I'm Erin DiBenedetto and I'm running for re-election to the Method School Committee.

709
01:03:55,449 --> 01:04:03,133
My goal as a committee member is to be a leader who has the experience and the relationships to deliver a solid innovation for Method.

710
01:04:04,493 --> 01:04:11,637
Having served three terms on the Method School Committee, I'm bringing my record of fighting for residents and community organizing to our city.

711
01:04:12,738 --> 01:04:20,100
As a school committee member, I commit to work to make sure everyone in our district has the opportunity to succeed.

712
01:04:20,920 --> 01:04:24,901
I promise to be that honest voice of reason for all our Meffitt children.

713
01:04:26,021 --> 01:04:34,763
My husband Joe and I moved to Meffitt in 1987 and raised our two children, both of which graduated from Meffitt High School.

714
01:04:35,623 --> 01:04:42,465
Joey is a graduate of Worcester State University and is getting his master's degree in public health

715
01:04:43,602 --> 01:04:49,967
And my Caitlin, she's a graduate of Tufts University and is getting her degree as a nurse practitioner.

716
01:04:51,268 --> 01:05:02,337
My job as a special education coordinator for Prospect Hill Academy, where I advocate for children, gives me a unique insight to improving our schools.

717
01:05:03,318 --> 01:05:07,561
I bring my knowledge of working in a school every day to our committee.

718
01:05:08,962 --> 01:05:12,025
In 2011, when my youngest graduated,

719
01:05:12,526 --> 01:05:21,593
I decided to run for Medford School Committee because my voice needed to be heard and because all children deserve the best education a city can offer.

720
01:05:23,635 --> 01:05:34,783
Some of the things that have been accomplished while working with other members of the committee have been to ensure we have a balanced budget with any need for supplemental appropriations.

721
01:05:35,704 --> 01:05:40,768
Our committee has creatively and resourcefully developed additional sources of revenue.

722
01:05:42,051 --> 01:05:50,253
The planning and implementation of technology upgrades and our new science labs at Meffitt High School are major accomplishments.

723
01:05:50,913 --> 01:06:00,155
These projects are not only offering the best education for our high school students, but they have increased programming for our vocational students.

724
01:06:01,115 --> 01:06:04,976
As a committee, we have reviewed new legislation regularly,

725
01:06:05,770 --> 01:06:13,255
Our committees have submitted medical emergency plans, concussion plans, and bullying plans to the state.

726
01:06:14,256 --> 01:06:20,620
Upgrades have been made at our Curtis Tufts School, as well as our Kids' Corner for our youngest learners.

727
01:06:21,280 --> 01:06:24,382
We have worked hard to keep our class size small.

728
01:06:25,443 --> 01:06:33,108
We have purchased new ELA and math programs for our elementary schools, and there have been many, many more accomplishments.

729
01:06:34,617 --> 01:06:46,022
When involved in interviewing and hiring our new principals or evaluating our superintendent, we always try to be the voice of the parents and the students in our community.

730
01:06:47,363 --> 01:06:50,905
While we have done some amazing work, there is much more to do.

731
01:06:51,625 --> 01:07:01,450
As a committee, we need to ensure our students are prepared to compete globally for spots at our country's best universities.

732
01:07:02,190 --> 01:07:14,698
We are responsible to make sure the programs offered to our children are supported with the material and the supplies needed for our students to have maximum access to the curriculum.

733
01:07:15,538 --> 01:07:22,903
We need to preserve our traditional vocational programs while we keep pace with the changing needs in our workforce.

734
01:07:23,864 --> 01:07:29,067
We need to analyze our testing scores and make sure we are meeting the needs of all our students

735
01:07:29,578 --> 01:07:32,799
So they all have every opportunity to excel.

736
01:07:34,120 --> 01:07:42,303
We need to build online learning opportunities so all students have a way to access the curriculum and we meet all our children's needs.

737
01:07:44,424 --> 01:07:52,227
We need to invest in our buildings to maintain them for the years to come while working to keep our students and staff safe.

738
01:07:53,305 --> 01:07:59,247
We need to have open communication with administration, teachers, students, and parents.

739
01:08:00,328 --> 01:08:12,413
In the coming years, this committee may be involved in hiring a new superintendent of schools, which I think is going to be one of the most important roles our future committee will be undertaking.

740
01:08:13,913 --> 01:08:22,377
I've learned from my many years of community involvement that some of the best ideas in government come from the neighborhoods, not the bureaucrats.

741
01:08:23,562 --> 01:08:35,745
That's why I'm asking you to reach out to me at 781-254-0095 with any ideas or concerns or ways that I can help you or your child.

742
01:08:36,805 --> 01:08:48,527
That's also a reason, while I am asking for your vote on November 7th to continue my work to be the honest voice of reason for all our Method children.

743
01:08:48,908 --> 01:08:49,328
Thank you.

744
01:08:49,348 --> 01:08:50,728
Thank you, Erin.

745
01:09:03,221 --> 01:09:03,781
Hi, everybody.

746
01:09:04,261 --> 01:09:08,302
My name is Kathy Miles-Kretz, and I'm running for re-election for Memphis School Committee.

747
01:09:08,682 --> 01:09:15,684
I just want to simply say thank you to Henley Miller and the Democratic Ward Committee for having this candidate night.

748
01:09:17,444 --> 01:09:22,305
So I'm running for re-election for Memphis School Committee, and I'm a Medford High School graduate.

749
01:09:22,405 --> 01:09:24,065
I grew up in Medford.

750
01:09:24,105 --> 01:09:26,106
My parents moved here when I was four months old.

751
01:09:26,706 --> 01:09:29,767
I went to the Waite School, which was the neighborhood school.

752
01:09:30,147 --> 01:09:31,347
I went to the Hobbs Junior High.

753
01:09:31,881 --> 01:09:35,043
I went to Medford High School and I graduated class of 1990.

754
01:09:35,663 --> 01:09:46,048
My husband graduated Medford Vocational one year before me and my son, like his dad, is enrolled in the Medford Vocational High School and he's enrolled in the robotics engineering program.

755
01:09:47,108 --> 01:09:52,031
Immediately after graduating high school, I went to college and I went to Suffolk University.

756
01:09:52,071 --> 01:10:00,655
I commuted and I worked two jobs while going to college so that I could maintain work and school and paying some of my education.

757
01:10:01,637 --> 01:10:05,098
After I graduated college, I immediately began working at State Street.

758
01:10:05,198 --> 01:10:18,804
I worked there for 13 years, and then shortly after my son, who I adopted, came over here from Korea, I wanted to work from home, so I established my own licensed family daycare business, so I could stay home and take care of him.

759
01:10:19,184 --> 01:10:23,365
When he went to kindergarten, I started working at Mass Teachers Retirement System.

760
01:10:24,286 --> 01:10:28,007
So shortly after my son moved on from middle school to high school,

761
01:10:28,547 --> 01:10:33,791
I missed the interactions at the elementary school and the middle school levels, and I was interested in running for school committee.

762
01:10:34,112 --> 01:10:36,274
So I ran the first time, and here I am running again.

763
01:10:37,374 --> 01:10:52,887
And some of the accomplishments that I have to talk about while I was on school committee in my first term were, I set out that for my plan was that I was going to go out to each and every school, meet with the principals, do a site tour, and do classroom observations.

764
01:10:53,048 --> 01:10:53,748
And I did that.

765
01:10:53,908 --> 01:10:54,769
I accomplished that.

766
01:10:55,223 --> 01:10:59,004
and I have some great stories to share about going to the classroom observations.

767
01:10:59,484 --> 01:11:23,971
I went out to each elementary school, and I went to the Roberts Elementary, and I sat through a little observation in the kindergarten where the students were doing K-Focus, and the little group I was put with was doing acting out dramatic play, The Three Little Pigs, and they were cutting out with construction paper, and they were kind of acting out The Three Little Pigs.

768
01:11:23,991 --> 01:11:24,871
It was just amazing.

769
01:11:25,325 --> 01:11:27,627
I've been to the Columbus Elementary School.

770
01:11:27,667 --> 01:11:29,348
The children were writing out commercials.

771
01:11:29,768 --> 01:11:35,792
Later that year, I was invited back to go see the commercials acted out, and they walked down the red carpet.

772
01:11:36,253 --> 01:11:44,178
I've been to the Brooks Elementary, where the students were dressed up to portray somebody in history, and they recited who they were representing.

773
01:11:44,678 --> 01:11:52,684
I've been to the McGlynn Elementary to see their hydroponics project, and the day I went, the lettuce that they were growing was ready to be cut,

774
01:11:53,068 --> 01:11:56,751
So we had a taste testing, and the students brought in some of their salad dressings.

775
01:11:57,211 --> 01:12:05,818
So one of my things that I've been doing is just going out to the schools and being there and seeing what the students are doing, working with the teachers and the administrators.

776
01:12:06,178 --> 01:12:07,499
And I want to continue doing that.

777
01:12:08,080 --> 01:12:10,482
I've been on field trips with the middle school.

778
01:12:10,942 --> 01:12:13,664
We went to the Museum of Science.

779
01:12:14,064 --> 01:12:15,946
I've been on a field trip with the high school.

780
01:12:15,986 --> 01:12:17,487
We went to the Day at the Hill.

781
01:12:17,867 --> 01:12:19,168
I want to continue to do that.

782
01:12:20,840 --> 01:12:24,264
I've been a very big advocate for the Medford Vocational Schools.

783
01:12:24,984 --> 01:12:26,426
We have 20 programs.

784
01:12:26,786 --> 01:12:30,370
We've reduced our students going to Minuteman, so we're saving money.

785
01:12:30,831 --> 01:12:35,476
We have a partnership with Everett, and we have tuition coming in from Everett.

786
01:12:35,496 --> 01:12:38,138
Students are taking courses at the Medford Vocational School.

787
01:12:38,659 --> 01:12:43,264
I'm on the Robotics Engineering Advisory Committee, and I'm just so very proud of

788
01:12:44,176 --> 01:12:46,618
all of the equipment that we have in our robotics shop.

789
01:12:46,658 --> 01:12:49,120
We started out with just 3D printers.

790
01:12:49,180 --> 01:13:04,290
We have a CNC, we have a mill, a lathe, we have a water jet, we have equipment that's industry ready that compares to some of our local colleges that I've seen when I've gone on college tours.

791
01:13:04,370 --> 01:13:10,274
It's just incredible what our students know and what they're learning right now, hands on.

792
01:13:10,614 --> 01:13:11,735
They're going on co-ops.

793
01:13:12,235 --> 01:13:19,720
at companies and they're earning above $6 above minimum wage right now while they're in high school seniors.

794
01:13:20,140 --> 01:13:20,841
It's incredible.

795
01:13:20,981 --> 01:13:32,909
I am so proud of our Medford Vocational and Medford High School and I'm happy to say that right now all of our students graduate from Medford High School, Medford Folk are now under one.

796
01:13:33,463 --> 01:13:36,605
And they can now access post-secondary education.

797
01:13:36,945 --> 01:13:38,006
They can go to college.

798
01:13:38,366 --> 01:13:39,726
They can go to career.

799
01:13:40,047 --> 01:13:41,247
They can go in the union.

800
01:13:41,928 --> 01:13:44,069
That option is there for all of our students.

801
01:13:44,209 --> 01:13:48,071
And we made that possible with the merger that just happened.

802
01:13:48,551 --> 01:13:49,812
There's still a lot to be done.

803
01:13:50,475 --> 01:13:58,280
and I look forward to the next couple of years, so I appreciate your vote for another term on the Memphis School Committee.

804
01:13:58,561 --> 01:13:59,361
Thank you very much.

805
01:13:59,401 --> 01:14:01,543
Remember to vote November 7th.

806
01:14:01,603 --> 01:14:03,804
Kathy Kretz, re-elect Memphis School Committee.

807
01:14:03,944 --> 01:14:04,825
Thank you very much.

808
01:14:05,445 --> 01:14:06,306
Thank you, Kathy.

